<%#
This code represents a modal component that prompts the user for confirmation before logging out.

The modal contains a modal dialog with a title, a close button, and a body that displays a confirmation message. 
The modal footer includes two buttons: the "Aceptar" button, which is a button_to helper that sends a DELETE request
to the destroy_user_session_path when clicked, and the "Cancelar" button, which dismisses the modal.

The modal is hidden by default and can be triggered by its ID "logoutModal". It allows the user to confirm or 
cancel the logout action.
%>

<div class="modal fade" id="logoutModal" tabindex="1" aria-labelledby="logoutModalLabel" aria-hidden="true">
    <div class="modal-dialog">
        <div class="modal-content">
            <div class="modal-header">
                <p class="modal-title fs-6" id="logoutModalLabel"><strong>Mensaje de confirmación</strong></p>
                <button type="button" class="btn-close" data-bs-dismiss="modal" aria-label="Close"></button>
            </div>
            <div class="modal-body d-flex flex-column gap-3">
                <h5>¿Está seguro(a) que desea cerrar sesión?</h5>
            </div>
            <div class="modal-footer d-flex justify-content-start">
                <%= button_to "Aceptar", destroy_user_session_path, method: :delete, data: { bs_dismiss: "modal" }, class: "button-primary"%>
                <button type="button" class="button-secondary w-auto" data-bs-dismiss="modal" aria-label="Close">Cancelar</button>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>